TITLE: SYSTEM CONSTANTS — ANALOG INPUT CARD TYPE, RANGE AND COEFFICIENTS
DB00801_St_ConstAiRawData is a static data block that holds a full set of range, parameter and
descriptive data for all types of analog input card channels.
Each dataset is stored in a structure of user data type: UT00801_St_ConstAiRawData.
This structure is configured to hold all the data required by the card itself, any module accessing
an analog input and any supervisory system that is to display the type and configuration of the
All the channel data is stored as constants and is used by all modules that have an interface
The purpose of the user data type and associated data block is to provide a consistent and
tested set of range, parameter and descriptive data that can be used directly by modules that
The ranges correspond to the numerical values returned by the card for a given type of analog
card signal. For example, a 4-20 mA card returns a numerical value of 0 at 4 mA ranging up to a
value of 27648 at 20 mA. The data specified in the UT00801 variable would have a lower limit of
In addition, each dataset contains the parametric data that defines the particular channel type
and can be used to set a particular analog input channel to a particular type and range during
runtime. Each dataset also contains a textual description of the channel type,:
e.g. Current – 4 wire (4 mA to 20 mA)
Finally, data associated with thermal resistance channel types also contain the real number
value of the spe-cific temperature coefficient that is to be applied to the channel.
